"As for sanity... now <strong>that's </strong>boring."></center</i></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/19/00 6:54:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/r/p/rpo2/Jzonn_Icon.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Conesus--- FFA planes or schedule</span><hr size=1> While it did have a few issues, the Karana system was a different one.  Planes where schedule a week at a time and all the big targets were put into a rotation.  Each week (on Thursdays), the guilds/alliances/organizations would scramble to claim their spot on the schedule.  Groups shouldn't schedule the same plane two weeks in a row and weekend days should not be grabbed continuously (a group shouldn't alternate Hate/Fear every Friday).  The rotations allowed a group up to 24 hours to take down the target (48 hours for gods), but they were supposed to make the attempt the first evening after spawn (however it happened). [Reader's Digest version.  Contact me if you want to see the full text of the Karana Guild Central charter.]<br>
<br>
No system can be enforced (not even FFA).  The groups on Karana chose to participate and that is why it worked.  It will take the same consideration from all the major groups on AR to put any system into place.  At the start, many of them won't be interested in a system of any kind.  I expect to see a fair amount of ranting for a while. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#004080">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Unguilded&gt;</B></FONT><BR>
<I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#ffffff">Ranger of Karana</I></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umeril.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meril</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/19/00 7:03:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/Meril?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Conesus--- FFA planes or schedule</span><hr size=1> That would be fine if it was a true council and not domineered like it was by Grey Hawke and thier Alliance partners.<br>
<br>
Personally one of the key reasons I left Karana was KGC, and I have no plans to jump into a new KGC type system anytime soon again, without a lot of input and discussion from all parties interested.<br>
<br>
I think for now we need to go with the flow get to know one another and then determine what will be needed to allow all persons of the new server a thriving and friendly enviroment.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Meril Zorin<br>
Eternal Wrath<br>
Lvl 57 Magette<br>
